      "message": "On 2008/11/11 10:36:11, David Turner wrote:\n\u003e I wonder why this is needed. does HOST_PREBUILT_TAG equal Linux on FreeBSD ?\n\nInitially, I\u0027ve made prebuilt/freebsd-x86 as symlink to prebuilt/linux-x86 to use linux prebuilts and there was problem with libraries in Linux compatibility mode. Now it\u0027s useless as I\u0027ve native prebuilded binaries for all execpt arm-eabi and emulator compiles successfully without ifneq FreeBSD. It\u0027s my mistake, I\u0027ll remove this condition.\n\nBy the way, distrib/update-audio.sh mentioned a little bit higher in this makefile uses perforce to submit library to depot. As publicly available sources of Android are in git-repository, this file seems obsolete and even confusing (especially, if you have set P4* environment variables for unrelated to Android depot)",
